A minimal Angular seed that you need to bootstrap.
No Jade included. Use plain HTML as templates.
Uses NodeJS as a web server and ExpressJS.
Either use grunt sass to compile css
Or compass watch to compile css

If you're using Ubuntu:

1.Install NodeJS
sudo apt-get install python-software-properties
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:chris-lea/node.js
sudo apt-get update

sudo apt-get install nodejs
sudo apt-get install npm

2. Install express
sudo npm install express

3. Install Compass
sudo apt-get install ruby-full
sudo apt-get install rubygems1.9
sudo gem install compass

4. Watch SASS
run 'compass watch' under public folder
Sass changes will be compiled into css files.

5. Install Grunt
run 'sudo npm install grunt'
